{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "PM 2.5 is a main pollutant of ambient air pollution.",
    "The adverse effect on lung health is mostly attributed to its smaller particle size, larger surface area, physical characteristics of the particles, and stronger activity.",
    "In addition, PM 2.5 may be composed of sulfur dioxide, sulfates, metals, nitrates, acids, and carbon particles with various chemicals adsorbed onto their surfaces (24).",
    "A recent study in an animal model demonstrated that PM 2.5 led to easier deposition into lung tissues compared with other pollutants (25).",
    "The deposition of PM 2.5 increases the expression of inflammatory cytokine by activating inflammatoryassociated cells and triggers oxida-tive stress by impairing the immune balance (25)."
  ],
